						<summary>

						<p>The date is given as Śubhakṛit, Puraṭṭādi, ba•• This seems to be an unfinished record, also built in at the right end, which mentions Śeyya Śivapūdaṇ Madiśūdanaṉ Vānavanāyakaṉ of Kōyambēḍu in Māṅgāṭṭu-nāḍu a division of Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻamaṇḍalam figuring as a donor in No. 574 above; and also the village Nirandanūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kulōttuṅgaśōḻa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Mēṟpākkai-nāḍu, a division of Adhirājēndra-maṇḍalam.</p>						

						</summary>
